label.value: inference of sequence features from visual inspection

value.value: A type of inferential evidence in which sequence features are inferred based on visual inspection of the sequence.

definition.value: This type of inference may be made by either a curator or an author.

label.value: machine learning method evidence

value.value: A type of computational evidence in which computational systems build models based on sample data, known as training data, in order to make predictions or decisions without being explicitly programmed to do so. Such systems are trained on a combination of existing data about an entity, and are applied to the generation of new labels, such as numerical or textual or categorical.

label.value: deep learning neural network method evidence

value.value: A type of neural network method evidence which leverages a broad suite of neural network models, which use a combination of data attributes of an entity called features as inputs, and map them to outputs through multiple layers of connected hidden units, whose parameters are learned from data.

label.value: rule-based machine learning method evidence

value.value: A type of machine learning method evidence which uses a combination of data attributes to derive knowledge used to create a set of rules. These rules collectively represent the prediction model and are in the form of "IF:THEN" statements. The knowledge applied can be traced back to the rules and the original data.

label.value: single molecule fluorescence in situ hybridization evidence

value.value: A type of fluorescence in situ hybridization evidence resulting from the use of fluorescent probes to localize and quantify individual RNA molecules in single cells for studying gene expression.

label.value: support vector machine evidence

value.value: A type of machine learning method evidence that uses a supervised learning model with associated algorithms for classification. Support vector machines aim to determine a hyperplane that separates two classes while maximizing the distance from the hyperplane to any given data point in those classes.

label.value: string-matching method evidence

value.value: A type of computational evidence that employs a string algorithm to identify a string within a larger string or body of text, where a string is a particular series of characters consisting of letters, numbers, symbols, spaces, etc.

label.value: regular expression method evidence

value.value: A type of string-matching method evidence in which patterns consisting of characters and/or symbols in particular combinations and/or order are used to identify matches in a larger string or body of text.

label.value: neural network method evidence

value.value: A type of machine learning method evidence in which the machine learning model consists of nodes connected to each other with edges that are organized into layers, where the edges can transmit signals between nodes such that the system acts similarly to biological neurons.

label.value: coordinate mapping to geographic property shapefiles

value.value: A type of computational inference where a geographic property of an entity is determined by searching coordinates associated with the entity against polygons with associated geographic properties in the form of shapefiles.

label.value: inference of intermediate molecular structure from structure of final molecule

value.value: A type of curator inference in which the structure of a possible intermediate molecule made during a biosynthetic process is inferred based on the structure of the final molecule in the process.
